article.headline: Drake 72, Evansville 65
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. -- Josh Young scored 18 points to lead Drake to a 72-65 victory over Evansville Wednesday night. Adam Templeton added 14 points, eight rebounds and four assists, and Frank Wiseler scored 12 points for the Bulldogs (9-11, 4-4), who have won four in a row in the Missouri Valley. Ryan Wedel had 10 points. Drake was 10-for-20 from 3-point range, led by Templeton who was 3-for-5. Young was successful on his only attempt from behind the arc. From inside the 3-point line, the Bulldogs were less accurate, making 12-of-29 shots. Denver Holmes led all scorers with 23 points for Evansville (6-12, 0-8). James Haarsma had 18 points and eight rebounds for the Aces while Colt Ryan had seven points, seven assists and eight rebounds.
